body.name: CORSAIR VENGEANCE DDR5 RAM 32GB (2x16GB) 6000MHz CL36 Intel XMP iCUE Compatible Computer Memory - Black (CMK32GX5M2D6000C36)
deliveryMessages: Or fastest delivery Wednesday, February 14. Order within 5 hrs 45 mins
features: Welcome to the Cutting-Edge of Performance: Push the limits of your system like never before with DDR5 memory, unlocking even faster frequencies, greater capacities, and better performance than previous generations.

Do it All, and Do it Faster: As modern CPUs feature more and more cores, the unprecedented speed of DDR5 ensures your high-end CPU gets data quickly, enabling faster processing, rendering, and buffering than ever before.
Onboard Voltage Regulation: Makes for easier, more finely-tuned, and more stable overclocking through CORSAIR iCUE software than previous generation motherboard control.
Custom Intel XMP 3.0 Profiles: Customize and save your own XMP profiles via iCUE to tailor performance by app or task for greater efficiency.
Powerful CORSAIR iCUE Software: Enables real-time frequency readings, onboard voltage regulation, and custom XMP profiles.
body.description: CORSAIR VENGEANCE DDR5, optimized for Intel motherboards, delivers the higher frequencies and greater capacities of DDR5 technology in a high-quality, compact module that suits your system. Tightly-screened high-frequency memory chips power your PC through faster processing, rendering, and buffering than ever, with onboard voltage regulation for easy, finely controlled overclocking. CORSAIR iCUE software enables real-time frequency monitoring, onboard voltage regulation, and Intel XMP 3.0 profile customization. A distinctive solid aluminum heatspreader keeps your memory cool, while ensuring wide compatibility with a huge range of motherboards and CPU coolers. With a limited lifetime warranty as your guarantee of reliability for years to come, VENGEANCE DDR5 continues a long-standing legacy of memory performance.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The one for COD MW Games
reviews.reviewText: I tried so many rams kits, from 4 stick (4x16) 6000MTs down to 2 sticks (2x16) 7200MTs to the latest 2x32 at 6600MTs and many CL speeds. 30CL 32CL 34CL and 36CL. Asus released max memory support and high speed on the ROG Z790 E-wifi on a bios update, then my 4 sticks did not work, status 55, I removed 2 sticks and worked fine, but stutters were visible. I tried the 2 sticks 72kMTs and Call of Duty crashed, I tried the 2x32 6600 I tried the regular 2 stick 2x16 5600MTs and same issue. Then I check the Asus support memory support page and every single ram brand were not compatible, of course. But even one that was compatible also did not work, the Corsair Vengeance 2x32 at 6600MTs. Then I read a post online that COD works perfectly with this configuration, 2x16GB 6000 36-36-36-76 1.35 I play and play non stop for 4-5 hours and no crashes. these below are the brands that were having issues in COD, and the last that doesn't.Team T-Force Delta RGB (2 x 16GB) 6000 FF3D532G6000HC30DC01 30-36-36-76 - does not workTeam T-Force Delta RGB (2 x 16GB) 7200 FF3D532G7200HC34ADC01 34-42-42-84 - does not workCORSAIR Vengeance 2 x 32GB) 6600 CMK64GX5M2B6600C32 32-39-39-76 - does not workG.SKILL Ripjaws S5 Series (2 x 16GB) 5600 F5-5600J2834F16GX2-RS5K 28-34-34-89 - does not workCORSAIR VENGEANCE (2x16GB) 6000 CMK32GX5M2D6000C36 36-36-36-76 - no issues. with XMPI hope this helps.

reviews.reviewTitle: Great performance, especially for the price
reviews.reviewText: This is a kit containing two matched 16GB sticks of DDR5-6000mhz RAM (32GB total). Timing is 36-36-36-76 (selected by my motherboard as default XMP). The overall profile of the ram is low, and I was able to install it easily despite one of the memory slots being encroached upon by my large CPU heatsink/fan.The black and grey heatsink has some interesting textures and should look good with almost any colour scheme. This RAM is assembled in Taiwan.I’m using this with my i7-13700K and Asus TUF Gaming Z690-Plus motherboard, and haven’t had any stability issues running at 6000MHz.I used UserBenchmark to create benchmarks with default XMP settings (see screenshot attached):Corsair Vengeance 2 x 16GB @ 6000MHz / 36-36-36-76 timing selected by XMPMulti-core Read/write/mixed/average (GB/s, higher is better): 80.2/75.7/71.9/75.9Single-core Rear/write/mixed/average (GB/s, higher is better): 23/52.7/33/36.2Latency – 66.6nsI also tried a using Crucial Pro 6000MHz RAM, but switched back to this as it performed better and was cheaper.Overall, I’m really happy with the price and performance.
Pues que puedo decir al final la marca es de renombre y funcionan como deben de funcionar, ningun fallo y son excelentes!!!!
